<span id="freeTextContainer911839679491193883">McPherson argues that ideals and duty were at the heart of why soldiers fought in the Civil War. It amazes me to see that the definitions of concepts such as “democracy” and “liberty” vary so much between Union and Confederate soldiers. It’s as if they were from different planets.</span>

